  "text": "Bellavista et al. [CITATION_1] studied a solution based on a middleware that balances between the proper level of user privacy and the needs of location-based services precision. The location data are, then, exposed at the proper level of granularity depending on privacy/efficiency requirements negotiated by the parties. Hence, instead of exact client positions, a downscaled location information (with lower precision and lower geographical granularity) is returned.",
